Muddle thyme, sage, oregano, rosemary, garlic salt, and salt together with a mortar and pestle. Pour vinegar into mortar bowl and swirl around to mix with herbs. Scoop egg yolks from eggs and transfer to a bowl; mash egg yolks using a fork until texture is very fine. Stir chives and black pepper into mashed egg yolks. Pour vinegar-herb mixture into egg yolks and mix well. Mix mayonnaise, sour cream, mustard, and sucralose sweetener into egg yolk mixture until smooth. Spoon egg yolk mixture into egg whites using a teaspoon.